Versioning and Template Management
  Setting Up Git Repositories for CloudFormation
  Example Structure:
  /cloudformation/
    ├── networking/
    │   ├── vpc.yaml
    │   ├── subnets.yaml
    ├── security/
    │   ├── security-groups.yaml
    ├── compute/
        ├── ec2.yaml
        ├── autoscaling.yaml
  Stack Updates and Change Set Management
    Creating and Executing Change Sets
    Example CLI Command:
      aws cloudformation create-change-set \
      --stack-name my-app-stack \
      --template-body file://updated-template.yaml \
      --change-set-name my-change-set
  Testing, Validating, and Auditing Templates
    Using cloudformation validate-template for Syntax Checking
    Example CLI command:
    aws cloudformation validate-template --template-body file://network-setup.yam
